main event: Several witnesses in Midland, Michigan observed four star-like objects in the sky that appeared to be following each other in an irregular formation on October 17, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as being larger than stars and brighter, and seemed to change direction and altitude while moving slowly toward the north.
It is possible that the objects were the Echo II satellite.
The witnesses were not sure what the objects were, as they did not appear to be any type of aircraft they were familiar with.
The objects were observed for about 50 minutes.
The witnesses were left with a feeling of awe and wonderment about what they had witnessed.
sighted object: four star-like objects in the sky
